section.para:
The tool can be run as a stand-alone command, using the launcher scripts runV3migrateJCas; 
	      there are two versions of this — one for windows (ending it ".bat") and one for linux / mac (ending in ".sh").
		    If you run this without any arguments, it will show a brief help for the arguments.

No matter how the tool is started, the input to the tool is one or more directory tree roots; 
	      the tool will scan the file system under these roots (including inside Jars and PEARs), 
	      looking for definitions to migrate.
